latestPosts.caption:
Life is a choice — and I chose me, over and over again.
My 16-year-old self would be so proud to see how far I’ve come. Stronger. Wiser. Still standing.

This video took me days to make. I cried while editing. I laughed writing the script. And through it all, I did it — because this was a gift to myself.

Here’s to another year of getting older, growing deeper, and choosing me every time.

Some say going back to your roots means returning to your origins.

For me, it’s not a place, it’s a person - my mother. On Mother’s Day, we honor the one who made us, shaped us, and loved us before we even knew what love was.

To all the Maas, Mummys, Ammis, - a very Happy Mother’s Day!

latestPosts.caption:
Life is overwhelming at times. The fluidity of getting older lies in learning to feel and admit our emotions. 
We crave slow living amidst the chaos of the city. 
We seek silence between the noise. 
We search for that one lasting connection—and admit that the feeling is both never-ending and a lie in itself.

Oh I love everything about summer ! The powder-blue skies, the warmth of creamy coffees, the golden hum of city yellows. 
Everything sings in harmony with the hues of a brown girl. 
And this kurta? A dreamy new favorite in my sun-soaked story.
Wearing @colorsofearth.in
